This is a planning board that is implemented in a large company.

01:26:40.000 --> 01:26:54.000
Please look, here are our plans for the day, plans for the week and plans for the month.

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:59.000
Please note, here is the planning for the month, the third line,

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:05.000
and the pillars of the performers who carry out these tasks.

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:12.000
And at the intersection, tasks that are recorded on stickers.

01:27:12.000 --> 01:27:17.000
Unfortunately, this is not reflected on the slide,

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:21.000
but in fact, in this company, above each name,

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:28.000
an envelope is also attached, in which tasks are added,

01:27:28.000 --> 01:27:32.000
that is, already used stickers.

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:38.000
And thus, having completed the task that we planned for the day,

01:27:38.000 --> 01:27:42.000
we just remove this sticker and move it to the envelope,

01:27:42.000 --> 01:27:47.000
and having looked through the list of our tasks for the week,

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:56.000
we take the one that is most relevant and most important for us to perform the next day,

01:27:56.000 --> 01:28:06.000
and just in a matter of seconds we glue it to the board in this section of tasks for the day.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:08.000
The same thing happens with the month.

01:28:08.000 --> 01:28:13.000
Please note the very interesting result of the work.

01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:19.000
After a month, all these envelopes are emptied,

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:29.000
and a meeting takes place where people sum up the tasks completed in a month.

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:36.000
The most interesting thing is that the person who has completed the most tasks receives a day off.

01:28:36.000 --> 01:28:44.000
Of course, these tasks are not fixed by a formal sign,

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:47.000
like, I took a piece of paper and put it on the other end of the table.

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:55.000
They are still comparable in their significance, in some weight, of course.

01:28:55.000 --> 01:29:04.000
So, the next technique is called the result-oriented planning.

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:08.000
Pay attention to the following slide.

01:29:08.000 --> 01:29:16.000
We are very often used to fixing our tasks in the following formulations.

01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:24.000
Call Ivanov. Petrov. Project. Meeting at 16.00.

01:29:24.000 --> 01:29:40.000
However, we can hardly understand the purpose of this event and what result we should get from these formulations.

01:29:40.000 --> 01:29:47.000
So, we suggest the result-oriented planning of your tasks.

01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:52.000
Instead of calling Ivanov, you should finish Ivanov's order.

01:29:52.000 --> 01:29:56.000
Instead of Petrov. Project, you should get Petrov's information.

01:29:56.000 --> 01:30:05.000
Instead of meeting at 16.00, you can use another formulation.

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:12.000
Not to make a joint, but to encourage, reward, praise, and so on.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:16.000
Please pay attention to the following item.

01:30:16.000 --> 01:30:18.000
This is prioritization.

01:30:18.000 --> 01:30:21.000
Why is this the Schwab method?

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:27.000
We are talking about the head of the company named Charles Schwab,

01:30:27.000 --> 01:30:35.000
who asked the consultant for help in optimizing his working day.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:42.000
He does not have time to perform the most important tasks for him.

01:30:42.000 --> 01:30:48.000
The consultant gave a very banal recommendation.

01:30:48.000 --> 01:30:54.000
Make a list of your priority tasks.

01:30:54.000 --> 01:31:00.000
First, make a list of the most important tasks.

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:06.000
And then make a list of the least important tasks.

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:10.000
And, please, perform these tasks in this sequence.

01:31:10.000 --> 01:31:15.000
Then, the tasks that you simply do not have enough time for,

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:21.000
will remain unimportant.

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:23.000
The most interesting is the result.

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:28.000
A couple of weeks later, the consultant received a check for $ 25,000

01:31:28.000 --> 01:31:36.000
with a remark that it was the most valuable management advice he had ever heard and received.

01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:41.000
Indeed, we remember the old metaphor.

01:31:41.000 --> 01:31:47.000
The metaphor about a vessel half filled with water.

01:31:47.000 --> 01:31:51.000
This is a resource of our working time.

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:57.000
And here are stones, pebbles, and sand.

01:31:57.000 --> 01:32:02.000
Stones are large, powerful, important tasks.

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:06.000
Pebbles are medium tasks.

01:32:06.000 --> 01:32:12.000
And finally, sand is not an important task.

01:32:12.000 --> 01:32:15.000
But there are many of them.

01:32:15.000 --> 01:32:21.000
And we really want to put as many pebbles as possible in the morning.

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:25.000
Decide to throw yourself off, to drop as many tasks as possible.

01:32:25.000 --> 01:32:31.000
And we do that by first filling our vessel with sand.

01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:34.000
And the water rises significantly.

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:36.000
Our working time is gone.

01:32:36.000 --> 01:32:39.000
After that, we start throwing pebbles there.

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:42.000
The water rose even more.

01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:48.000
And when it came to starting to immerse stones there,

01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:51.000
the water began to overflow across the edge.

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:57.000
We stayed there at the end of our working time at our workplaces.

01:32:57.000 --> 01:33:00.000
And we put stones there.

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:04.000
And now it's 7, 8, 9 o'clock.

01:33:04.000 --> 01:33:07.000
And there are no stones at the end of the edge.

01:33:07.000 --> 01:33:10.000
And it's already night outside.

01:33:10.000 --> 01:33:14.000
So, what are the recommendations in this regard?

01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:17.000
As for prioritizing tasks,

01:33:17.000 --> 01:33:21.000
put the most important thing first.

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:26.000
You put two stones, and the water rose very much.

01:33:26.000 --> 01:33:29.000
You spent a lot of your working time.

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:31.000
After that, pour pebbles there.

01:33:31.000 --> 01:33:33.000
The water will rise completely.

01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:38.000
And finally, pour sand until the water has reached the edge.

01:33:38.000 --> 01:33:41.000
And when the water has reached the edge,

01:33:41.000 --> 01:33:45.000
that is, your working time has exhausted itself,

01:33:45.000 --> 01:33:49.000
make a decision whether this sand is worth it

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:55.000
to stay for it at your workplace,

01:33:55.000 --> 01:34:00.000
when it's already evening and when we're waiting at home.

01:34:00.000 --> 01:34:03.000
So, it should be noted

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:06.000
the differentiability of such concepts

01:34:06.000 --> 01:34:10.000
as the result of orientation and concretization.

01:34:10.000 --> 01:34:12.000
Attention to the next slide.

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:17.000
Please look at this graph.

01:34:17.000 --> 01:34:21.000
At the bottom, in the left corner, you have a meeting.

01:34:21.000 --> 01:34:24.000
It's a neutral recording.

01:34:24.000 --> 01:34:28.000
It's not result-oriented and not concretized.

01:34:28.000 --> 01:34:34.000
You start moving horizontally

01:34:34.000 --> 01:34:37.000
and intensify the concretization.

01:34:37.000 --> 01:34:39.000
You have the following recording.

01:34:39.000 --> 01:34:43.000
A meeting on project A, which will take place at 4 p.m.

01:34:43.000 --> 01:34:47.000
in a kind of negotiating room with such people.

01:34:47.000 --> 01:34:51.000
Yes, the recording has become more concrete,

01:34:51.000 --> 01:34:55.000
but it still has no result.

01:34:55.000 --> 01:34:59.000
What do you want to get as a result of the meeting?

01:34:59.000 --> 01:35:03.000
And so we start moving vertically up.

01:35:03.000 --> 01:35:08.000
We begin to increase the result-orientedness of the phrase.

01:35:08.000 --> 01:35:15.000
Here you see a rough, let's say,

01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:18.000
a formulating of project A.

01:35:18.000 --> 01:35:21.000
In fact, you need to give a kick.

01:35:21.000 --> 01:35:25.000
In the upper right corner,

01:35:25.000 --> 01:35:29.000
you have a high result-orientedness

01:35:29.000 --> 01:35:33.000
and a high degree of concretization of the task.

01:35:33.000 --> 01:35:36.000
When you determine, first of all,

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:39.000
the result you need to get,

01:35:39.000 --> 01:35:41.000
the goal of the meeting,

01:35:41.000 --> 01:35:47.000
and finally the meeting, where it is, when and with whom it should take place.

01:35:47.000 --> 01:35:54.000
And now let's look at our workbook.

01:35:54.000 --> 01:36:00.000
Please open the workbook on page 8.

01:36:00.000 --> 01:36:04.000
Here are various formulations,

01:36:04.000 --> 01:36:09.000
both result-oriented and not result-oriented.

01:36:09.000 --> 01:36:12.000
Our task is to find the formulations

01:36:12.000 --> 01:36:16.000
that are not result-oriented

01:36:16.000 --> 01:36:21.000
and re-formulate them into a result-oriented type.

01:36:21.000 --> 01:36:25.000
Let's go straight in order.

01:36:25.000 --> 01:36:28.000
So, hand over the coat to the chemical cleaner.

01:36:28.000 --> 01:36:31.000
Undoubtedly, the result-oriented formulation.

01:36:31.000 --> 01:36:37.000
Because if we leave such a note on the table,

01:36:37.000 --> 01:36:41.000
that is, we ask our family members about it,

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:44.000
in the evening we can easily check it.

01:36:44.000 --> 01:36:46.000
Did you hand it over?

01:36:46.000 --> 01:36:48.000
Handed over. Everything is fine.

01:36:48.000 --> 01:36:52.000
So, the next point is to call Petrov.

01:36:52.000 --> 01:36:54.000
Please note,

01:36:54.000 --> 01:36:58.000
by logic, this is a result-oriented formulation,

01:36:58.000 --> 01:37:03.000
because it contains the necessary verb,

01:37:04.000 --> 01:37:11.000
which indicates the result that should be achieved

01:37:11.000 --> 01:37:14.000
and allows us to control later,

01:37:14.000 --> 01:37:18.000
in fact, whether we called or not.

01:37:18.000 --> 01:37:21.000
However, we note that in this case

01:37:21.000 --> 01:37:26.000
the very concretization of the formulation is necessary,

01:37:26.000 --> 01:37:33.000
because the very purpose of the call may not be the fact itself.

01:37:33.000 --> 01:37:37.000
Most likely, we expect something from this call,

01:37:37.000 --> 01:37:39.000
and what we expect from it,

01:37:39.000 --> 01:37:44.000
we would like to see in the formulation of the task itself.

01:37:44.000 --> 01:37:48.000
To achieve the signing of the contract with the OTC,

01:37:48.000 --> 01:37:52.000
of course, the result-oriented formulation,

01:37:52.000 --> 01:37:56.000
to transfer 15,000 to the account of the supplier,

01:37:56.000 --> 01:37:59.000
and also the result-oriented formulation,

01:37:59.000 --> 01:38:02.000
to meet with Konstantin.

01:38:02.000 --> 01:38:07.000
Of course, in these formulations a lot depends on the context.

01:38:07.000 --> 01:38:11.000
If Konstantin is our friend,

01:38:11.000 --> 01:38:15.000
and the task itself is to meet with him,

01:38:15.000 --> 01:38:17.000
to talk to him,

01:38:17.000 --> 01:38:20.000
to drink beer, and so on,

01:38:20.000 --> 01:38:23.000
then, of course, we can consider this formulation

01:38:23.000 --> 01:38:25.000
quite result-oriented.

01:38:25.000 --> 01:38:28.000
If we are talking about a work task,

01:38:28.000 --> 01:38:34.000
and some certain business hopes are laid out for this meeting,

01:38:34.000 --> 01:38:38.000
then we would like to formulate them

01:38:38.000 --> 01:38:41.000
directly in this formulation.

01:38:41.000 --> 01:38:42.000
Further.

01:38:42.000 --> 01:38:45.000
Meeting 15,000 employees.

01:38:45.000 --> 01:38:48.000
Not a result-oriented formulation,

01:38:48.000 --> 01:38:52.000
because we need to note

01:38:52.000 --> 01:38:56.000
what we expect from this meeting,

01:38:56.000 --> 01:38:59.000
and how we can understand

01:38:59.000 --> 01:39:03.000
whether this meeting was successful.

01:39:03.000 --> 01:39:08.000
Please note that many of our meetings

01:39:08.000 --> 01:39:16.000
are not 100% effective, unfortunately.

01:39:16.000 --> 01:39:18.000
For this reason.

01:39:18.000 --> 01:39:23.000
Because when organizing a meeting,

01:39:23.000 --> 01:39:29.000
we do not clearly represent the results

01:39:29.000 --> 01:39:32.000
that should be obtained.

01:39:32.000 --> 01:39:33.000
Next.

01:39:33.000 --> 01:39:37.000
Meeting at 13.00 is a result-oriented task.

01:39:37.000 --> 01:39:41.000
Just like making a schedule for tomorrow

01:39:41.000 --> 01:39:45.000
and going to the cinema in the evening.

01:39:45.000 --> 01:39:46.000
Next.

01:39:46.000 --> 01:39:51.000
Calling the client T to find out what the problem is.

01:39:51.000 --> 01:39:55.000
Quite a result-oriented formulation.

01:39:55.000 --> 01:39:56.000
We can check,

01:39:56.000 --> 01:39:59.000
you called, you called, you found out,

01:39:59.000 --> 01:40:01.000
found out, and great.

01:40:01.000 --> 01:40:02.000
Next.

01:40:02.000 --> 01:40:03.000
Object R.

01:40:03.000 --> 01:40:05.000
What to do with it?

01:40:05.000 --> 01:40:07.000
And here you need to understand,

01:40:07.000 --> 01:40:09.000
what to do with it?

01:40:09.000 --> 01:40:12.000
Decide what to do with it, right?

01:40:12.000 --> 01:40:15.000
To agree on what to do with it,

01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:18.000
discuss what to do with it,

01:40:18.000 --> 01:40:24.000
so that this formulation is not a result-oriented.

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:26.000
To sleep.

01:40:26.000 --> 01:40:28.000
As a rule, in training,

01:40:28.000 --> 01:40:33.000
this extremely simple point causes a lot of discussion.

01:40:33.000 --> 01:40:34.000
People say,

01:40:34.000 --> 01:40:37.000
no, it's not at all,

01:40:37.000 --> 01:40:41.000
I need to write exactly how much to lie down,

01:40:41.000 --> 01:40:42.000
how much to get up.

01:40:42.000 --> 01:40:44.000
In fact, what's the harm in hiding?

01:40:44.000 --> 01:40:48.000
This is a result-oriented formulation,

01:40:48.000 --> 01:40:52.000
and we can still find out for ourselves,

01:40:52.000 --> 01:40:57.000
whether we have achieved the result or not.

01:40:57.000 --> 01:40:58.000
Staying with children.

01:40:58.000 --> 01:41:01.000
Result-oriented formulation.

01:41:01.000 --> 01:41:02.000
Meeting Ivanov.

01:41:02.000 --> 01:41:03.000
Contract.

01:41:03.000 --> 01:41:06.000
Not a result-oriented formulation,

01:41:06.000 --> 01:41:12.000
because we need to understand what we expect from Ivanov in connection with this contract.

01:41:12.000 --> 01:41:19.000
We need to discuss it, sign, cancel, correct, and so on.

01:41:19.000 --> 01:41:21.000
16.00.

01:41:21.000 --> 01:41:23.000
Board of Directors Meeting.

01:41:23.000 --> 01:41:24.000
Exactly the same.

01:41:24.000 --> 01:41:26.000
Not a result-oriented formulation,

01:41:26.000 --> 01:41:30.000
because we still need to understand what we want.

01:41:30.000 --> 01:41:33.000
We need to organize this meeting,

01:41:33.000 --> 01:41:36.000
we need to prepare the transfer material,

01:41:36.000 --> 01:41:38.000
we need to prepare some kind of send-off,

01:41:38.000 --> 01:41:42.000
we need to speak at the Board of Directors Meeting, and so on.

01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:45.000
Withdraw money from AR-Media.

01:41:45.000 --> 01:41:48.000
Quite a result-oriented formulation.

01:41:48.000 --> 01:41:51.000
Letaev-Pronin calls.

01:41:51.000 --> 01:41:54.000
Not a result-oriented formulation,

01:41:54.000 --> 01:41:57.000
because we need to decide

01:41:57.000 --> 01:42:04.000
what we want to get from Letaev and Pronin as a result of these calls.

01:42:04.000 --> 01:42:12.000
For example, calls to discuss the contract with Letaev

01:42:12.000 --> 01:42:18.000
and sign this contract with Pronin.

01:42:18.000 --> 01:42:20.000
Remind yourself of the Board of Directors Meeting.

01:42:20.000 --> 01:42:24.000
Quite a result-oriented formulation.

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:27.000
Again, we have a dubious wording,

01:42:27.000 --> 01:42:31.000
but unfortunately it is very often used in our diaries.

01:42:31.000 --> 01:42:34.000
Cancel the event in Vyaz.

01:42:34.000 --> 01:42:37.000
So, ignore this event,

01:42:37.000 --> 01:42:39.000
do not go to it,

01:42:39.000 --> 01:42:40.000
come up with a reason.

01:42:40.000 --> 01:42:43.000
Quite a result-oriented formulation.

01:42:43.000 --> 01:42:44.000
And finally, the exhibition.

01:42:44.000 --> 01:42:47.000
Project B and Project C.

01:42:47.000 --> 01:42:50.000
Not a result-oriented formulation,

01:42:50.000 --> 01:42:54.000
but a formulation that we should note.

01:42:54.000 --> 01:42:56.000
What do we want?

01:42:56.000 --> 01:43:03.000
For example, to prepare for the exhibition with Project B and C.

01:43:03.000 --> 01:43:08.000
Prepare the standees for Project B

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:11.000
and the distribution materials for Project C.

01:43:11.000 --> 01:43:13.000
And so on.

01:43:13.000 --> 01:43:18.000
We should note that with a result-oriented formulation

01:43:18.000 --> 01:43:23.000
everything is not as transparent as with a concretization.

01:43:23.000 --> 01:43:30.000
And we are always very drawn to concretize some tasks

01:43:30.000 --> 01:43:34.000
much more than to orient the results of these tasks.

01:43:34.000 --> 01:43:41.000
But in fact, in order to get results

01:43:41.000 --> 01:43:43.000
on these tasks,

01:43:43.000 --> 01:43:48.000
we should focus not so much on the concretization,

01:43:48.000 --> 01:43:53.000
but on the result-orientedness of these formulations.

01:43:53.000 --> 01:43:57.000
And the specifics depend on each of us.

01:43:57.000 --> 01:44:03.000
So, we move on to planning our day.

01:44:03.000 --> 01:44:05.000
And first of all,

01:44:05.000 --> 01:44:11.000
we need to select the types of our daily tasks

01:44:11.000 --> 01:44:14.000
that we need to plan.

01:44:14.000 --> 01:44:17.000
Please, pay attention to the next slide.

01:44:17.000 --> 01:44:21.000
So, the types of our daily tasks.

01:44:21.000 --> 01:44:26.000
The first is the tough tasks that we are used to.

01:44:26.000 --> 01:44:31.000
These are tasks that are tied to our exact time.

01:44:32.000 --> 01:44:37.000
A meeting at 12 a.m. is a tough task.

01:44:37.000 --> 01:44:42.000
A presentation at 4 p.m. is a tough task.

01:44:42.000 --> 01:44:45.000
What to do with this tough task?

01:44:45.000 --> 01:44:47.000
Of course, as we are used to,

01:44:47.000 --> 01:44:50.000
we need to fix this task in our diary

01:44:50.000 --> 01:44:53.000
with a binding to the exact time.

01:44:53.000 --> 01:44:56.000
A meeting at 12 p.m.

01:44:56.000 --> 01:44:59.000
A presentation at 4 p.m.

01:44:59.000 --> 01:45:04.000
But we also have flexible tasks.

01:45:04.000 --> 01:45:06.000
What are they?

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:10.000
These are tasks that we must do today.

01:45:10.000 --> 01:45:13.000
In this regard, they are not different from the tough ones.

01:45:13.000 --> 01:45:17.000
They are different in that their execution

01:45:17.000 --> 01:45:22.000
is not tied to a specific time.

01:45:22.000 --> 01:45:25.000
For example, making several calls,

01:45:25.000 --> 01:45:28.000
preparing some references,

01:45:28.000 --> 01:45:30.000
writing a report.

01:45:30.000 --> 01:45:36.000
In this regard, we should not overload our grid.

01:45:36.000 --> 01:45:43.000
We should simply make a list of these tasks,

01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:47.000
arranging them by priorities.

01:45:47.000 --> 01:45:50.000
That is, we will have flexible tasks

01:45:50.000 --> 01:45:52.000
starting with more priority ones

01:45:52.000 --> 01:45:57.000
and ending with less priority tasks.

01:45:57.000 --> 01:46:00.000
Among our flexible tasks,

01:46:00.000 --> 01:46:04.000
there are special flexible tasks.

01:46:04.000 --> 01:46:09.000
These are tasks that will take us a lot of time.

01:46:09.000 --> 01:46:12.000
For example, making a report.

01:46:12.000 --> 01:46:15.000
We know that we will do this

01:46:15.000 --> 01:46:18.000
for at least two hours.

01:46:18.000 --> 01:46:20.000
It does not matter to us

01:46:20.000 --> 01:46:22.000
when we will do this task,

01:46:22.000 --> 01:46:26.000
today at 12 p.m. or today at 3 p.m.

